      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorize the premium-root -IBLE words:</span> FLEXIBLE (X=8), CRUCIBLE (CC), HORRIBLE (H=4), TERRIBLE (R+R) — these are your high-value targets. The list is shorter than -ABLE so easier to learn.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">I-B-L-E stem recognition:</span> When you see I, B, L, E on your rack alongside premium consonants (F, X, H, V, C), check for -IBLE words first — they typically outscore -ABLE alternatives.</p></div>
